      <h1 class='title'>Electricity (Trading and Transmission) Bill</h1>
    </div>
    <div class='commons-written-statements-sitting' id='content'>
      
      <cite class='section'>HC Deb 30 January 2003 vol 398 c49WS</cite>
      <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_49ws' title='Col. 49WS &mdash; HC Deb 30 January 2003 vol 398 c49WS' name='column_49ws' href='#column_49ws' rel='bookmark'>49WS</a>
      <div class='hentry member_contribution'>
        <a name='S6CV0398P2_20030130_CWS_8'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/mr-brian-wilson' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S6CV0398P2_20030130_CWS_8' title='Link to this speech by Mr Brian Wilson' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
          <cite class='member author entry-title'><a href="/people/mr-brian-wilson" title="Mr Brian Wilson">The Minister for Energy and Construction (Mr. Brian Wilson)</a></cite>
          <p class="first-para">The draft <a href="/bills/electricity-trading-and-transmission-bill">Electricity (Trading and Transmission) Bill</a>, which will bring forward the British Electricity Transmission and Trading Arrangements (BETTA), is being published today. The Trade and Industry Committee will now undertake pre-legislative scrutiny of the Bill and will issue a report by Easter.</p><p>Copies of the draft Bill and draft Explanatory Notes are available in the House Library. A Regulatory Impact Assessment has been published on DTI and Ofgem's websites.</p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
